<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-245-150 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 784 163</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 10 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: Viewdata software for OS/2 PM. (Abacus Software'sVdial/PM) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Abacus Software (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Vdial/PM (Videotex software) (Product introduction)OS/2 Presentation Manager (Graphical user interface) (Equipmentand supplies).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionVideotexCommunications SoftwareOn-Line.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: Viewdata Software For OS/2 PM 01/10/91 LONDON, ENGLAND, 1991 JAN10 (NB) -- Abacus has announced Vdial/PM, which it claims is the firstdial-up viewdata software for OS/2 Presentation Manager.andP;  The software isbilled as a communications package that allows users on OS/2 networks toaccess videotex/viewdata online services.andP;  According to Abacus, the softwareallows users to dispense with existing viewdata and airline terminals, andinstall an OS/2 network.andP;  This will, the company claims, provide access toviewdata and well as VT100 (scrolling ASCII) online services.andM;&quot;Pricing is around the UKP 350 mark per station for a small number of users.andO;For large system users, the price is negotiable,&quot; Steve Feigen of Abacus toldNewsbytes.andM;The package was originally developed by Abacus for the Amadeus airlinereservation network, which is jointly owned by Air France, Iberia, Lufthansaand SAS.andM;Vdial/PM runs on a stand-alone PC as well as on a server supporting a LANManager network.andP;  For each external connection, the user will usually requireand autodial modem, but support for an internal X.25 controller is alsoavailable.andM;(Steve Gold/19910901/Press andamp; Public Contact: Steve Feigen, Abacus Software -Tel: 071-930-4884)</TEXT></DOC>